acceptAlert.name: accept alert
acceptAlert.description: Affects a currently showing alert. This command instructs Selenium to accept it.

acceptConfirmation.name: accept confirmation
acceptConfirmation.description: Affects a currently showing confirmation alert. This command instructs Selenium to accept it.

addSelection.name: add selection
addSelection.description: Add a selection to the set of options in a multi-select element.

answerPrompt.name: answer prompt
answerPrompt.description: Affects a currently showing alert prompt. This command instructs Selenium to provide the specified answer to it.

assert.name: assert
assert.description: Check that a variable is an expected value. The variables value will be converted to a string for comparison. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertAlert.name: assert alert
assertAlert.description: Confirm that an alert has been rendered with the provided text. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertChecked.name: assert checked
assertChecked.description: Confirm that the target element has been checked. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertConfirmation.name: assert confirmation
assertConfirmation.description: Confirm that a confirmation has been rendered. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertEditable.name: assert editable
assertEditable.description: Confirm that the target element is editable. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertElementPresent.name: assert element present
assertElementPresent.description: Confirm that the target element is present somewhere on the page. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertElementNotPresent.name: assert element not present
assertElementNotPresent.description: Confirm that the target element is not present anywhere on the page. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertNotChecked.name: assert not checked
assertNotChecked.description: Confirm that the target element has not been checked. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertNotEditable.name: assert not editable
assertNotEditable.description: Confirm that the target element is not editable. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertNotSelectedValue.name: assert not selected value
assertNotSelectedValue.description: Confirm that the value attribute of the selected option in a dropdown element does not contain the provided value. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertNotText.name: assert not text
assertNotText.description: Confirm that the text of an element does not contain the provided value.The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertPrompt.name: assert prompt
assertPrompt.description: Confirm that a JavaScript prompt has been rendered. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertSelectedValue.name: assert selected value
assertSelectedValue.description: Confirm that the value attribute of the selected option in a dropdown element contains the provided value. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertSelectedLabel.name: assert selected label
assertSelectedLabel.description: Confirm that the label of the selected option in a dropdown element contains the provided value. The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertText.name: assert text
assertText.description: Confirm that the text of an element contains the provided value.The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertTitle.name: assert title
assertTitle.description: Confirm the title of the current page contains the provided text.The test will stop if the assert fails.

assertValue.name: assert value
assertValue.description: Confirm the (whitespace-trimmed) value of an input field (or anything else with a value parameter). For checkbox/radio elementsthe value will be on or off depending on whether the element ischecked or not. The test will stop if the assert fails.

dismissConfirmation.name: dismiss confirmation
dismissConfirmation.description: Affects a currently showing confirmation alert. This command instructs Selenium to dismiss it.

dismissPrompt.name: dismiss prompt
dismissPrompt.description: Affects a currently showing alert prompt. This command instructs Selenium to dismiss it.

click.name: click
click.description: Clicks on a target element (e.g. a link button checkbox or radio button).

clickAt.name: click at
clickAt.description: Clicks on a target element (e.g. a link button checkbox or radio button). The coordinates are relative to the target element(e.g. 00 is the top left corner of the element) and are mostly usedto check effects that relay on them for example the material ripple effect.

close.name: close
close.description: Closes the current window. There is no need to close the initial window IDE will re-use it; closing it may cause a performancepenalty on the test.

debugger.name: debugger
debugger.description: Breaks the execution and enters debugger

do.name: do
do.description: Create a loop that executes the proceeding commands at least once. Terminate the branch with the repeat if command.

doubleClick.name: double click
doubleClick.description: Double clicks on an element (e.g. a link button checkbox or radio button).

doubleClickAt.name: double click at
doubleClickAt.description: Double clicks on a target element (e.g. a link button checkbox or radio button). The coordinates are relative to the targetelement (e.g. 00 is the top left corner of the element) and are mostlyused to check effects that relay on them for example the materialripple effect.

dragAndDropToObject.name: drag and drop to object
dragAndDropToObject.description: Drags an element and drops it on another element.

echo.name: echo
echo.description: Prints the specified message into the third table cell in your Selenese tables. Useful for debugging.

editContent.name: edit content
editContent.description: Sets the value of a content editable element as if you typed in it.

else.name: else
else.description: Part of an if block. Execute the commands in this branch when an if and/or else if condition are not met. Terminate the branchwith the end command.

elseIf.name: else if
elseIf.description: Part of an if block. Execute the commands in this branch when an if condition has not been met. Terminate the branch with theend command.

end.name: end
end.description: Terminates a control flow block for if while and times.

executeScript.name: execute script
executeScript.description: Executes a snippet of JavaScript in the context of the currently selected frame or window. The script fragment will be executedas the body of an anonymous function.  To store the return value usethe return keyword and provide a variable name in the value input field.

executeAsyncScript.name: execute async script
executeAsyncScript.description: Executes an async snippet of JavaScript in the context of the currently selected frame or window. The script fragment will beexecuted as the body of an anonymous function and must return a Promise.The Promise result will be saved on the variable if you use the returnkeyword.

forEach.name: for each
forEach.description: Create a loop that executes the proceeding commands for each item in a given collection.

if.name: if
if.description: Create a conditional branch in your test. Terminate the branch with the end command.

mouseDown.name: mouse down
mouseDown.description: Simulates a user pressing the left mouse button (without releasing it yet).

mouseDownAt.name: mouse down at
mouseDownAt.description: Simulates a user pressing the left mouse button (without releasing it yet) at the specified location.

mouseMoveAt.name: mouse move at
mouseMoveAt.description: Simulates a user pressing the mouse button (without releasing it yet) on the specified element.

mouseOut.name: mouse out
mouseOut.description: Simulates a user moving the mouse pointer away from the specified element.

mouseOver.name: mouse over
mouseOver.description: Simulates a user hovering a mouse over the specified element.

mouseUp.name: mouse up
mouseUp.description: Simulates the event that occurs when the user releases the mouse button (e.g. stops holding the button down).

mouseUpAt.name: mouse up at
mouseUpAt.description: Simulates the event that occurs when the user releases the mouse button (e.g. stops holding the button down) at the specified location.

open.name: open
open.description: Opens a URL and waits for the page to load before proceeding. This accepts both relative and absolute URLs.

pause.name: pause
pause.description: Wait for the specified amount of time.

removeSelection.name: remove selection
removeSelection.description: Remove a selection from the set of selected options in a multi-select element using an option locator.

repeatIf.name: repeat if
repeatIf.description: Terminate a do control flow branch conditionally. If the result of the provided conditional expression is true it startsthe do loop over.  Otherwise it ends the loop.

run.name: run
run.description: Runs a test case from the current project.

runScript.name: run script
runScript.description: Creates a new script tag in the body of the current test window and adds the specified text into the body of the command.Beware that JS exceptions thrown in these script tags arent managedby Selenium so you should probably wrap your script in try/catch blocksif there is any chance that the script will throw an exception.

select.name: select
select.description: Select an element from a drop-down menu using an option locator. Option locators provide different ways of specifying a selectelement (e.g. label= value= id= index=). If no option locator prefixis provided a match on the label will be attempted.

selectFrame.name: select frame
selectFrame.description: Selects a frame within the current window. You may invoke

selectWindow.name: select window
selectWindow.description: Selects a popup window using a window locator. Once a popup window has been selected all commands will go to that window.Window locators use handles to select windows.

sendKeys.name: send keys
sendKeys.description: Simulates keystroke events on the specified element as though you typed the value key-by-key. This simulates a real user typingevery character in the specified string; it is also bound by thelimitations of a real user like not being able to type into a invisibleor read only elements.  This is useful for dynamic UI widgets (likeauto-completing combo boxes) that require explicit key events. Unlikethe simple type command which forces the specified value into thepage directly this command will not replace the existing content.

setSpeed.name: set speed
setSpeed.description: Set execution speed (e.g. set the millisecond length of a delay which will follow each Selenium operation). By default thereis no such delay e.g. the delay is 0 milliseconds. This setting isglobal and will affect all test runs until changed.

setWindowSize.name: set window size
setWindowSize.description: Set the browsers window size including the browsers interface.

store.name: store
store.description: Save a target string as a variable for easy re-use.

storeAttribute.name: store attribute
storeAttribute.description: Gets the value of an element attribute. The value of the attribute may differ across browsers (this is the case for the styleattribute for example).

storeElementCount.name: store element count
storeElementCount.description: Gets the number of nodes that match the specified locator (e.g. xpath=//table would give the number of tables).

storeJson.name: store json
storeJson.description: Ssave JSON as an object on a variable

storeText.name: store text
storeText.description: Gets the text of an element and stores it for later use. This works for any element that contains text.

storeTitle.name: store title
storeTitle.description: Gets the title of the current page.

storeValue.name: store value
storeValue.description: Gets the value of element and stores it for later use. This works for any input type element.

storeWindowHandle.name: store window handle
storeWindowHandle.description: Gets the handle of the current page.

times.name: times
times.description: Create a loop that executes the proceeding commands n number of times.

type.name: type
type.description: Sets the value of an input field as though you typed it in. Can also be used to set the value of combo boxes check boxes etc.In these cases value should be the value of the option selected not

verify.name: verify
verify.description: Soft assert that a variable is an expected value. The variables value will be converted to a string for comparison.The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyChecked.name: verify checked
verifyChecked.description: Soft assert that a toggle-button (checkbox/radio) has been checked.The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyEditable.name: verify editable
verifyEditable.description: Soft assert whether the specified input element is editable (e.g. hasnt been disabled). The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyElementPresent.name: verify element present
verifyElementPresent.description: Soft assert that the specified element is somewhere on the page.The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyElementNotPresent.name: verify element not present
verifyElementNotPresent.description: Soft assert that the specified element is not somewhere on the page.The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyNotChecked.name: verify not checked
verifyNotChecked.description: Soft assert that a toggle-button (checkbox/radio) has not been checked.The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyNotEditable.name: verify not editable
verifyNotEditable.description: Soft assert whether the specified input element is not editable (e.g. hasnt been disabled). The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyNotSelectedValue.name: verify not selected value
verifyNotSelectedValue.description: Soft assert that the expected element has not been chosen in a select menu by its option attribute. The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyNotText.name: verify not text
verifyNotText.description: Soft assert the text of an element is not present. The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifySelectedLabel.name: verify selected label
verifySelectedLabel.description: Soft assert the visible text for a selected option in the specified select element. The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifySelectedValue.name: verify selected value
verifySelectedValue.description: Soft assert that the expected element has been chosen in a select menu by its option attribute. The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyText.name: verify text
verifyText.description: Soft assert the text of an element is present. The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyTitle.name: verify title
verifyTitle.description: Soft assert the title of the current page contains the provided text. The test will continue even if the verify fails.

verifyValue.name: verify value
verifyValue.description: Soft assert the (whitespace-trimmed) value of an input field (or anything else with a value parameter). For checkbox/radioelements the value will be on or off depending on whether theelement is checked or not. The test will continue even if the verify fails.

waitForElementEditable.name: wait for element editable
waitForElementEditable.description: Wait for an element to be editable.

waitForElementNotEditable.name: wait for element not editable
waitForElementNotEditable.description: Wait for an element to not be editable.

waitForElementNotPresent.name: wait for element not present
waitForElementNotPresent.description: Wait for a target element to not be present on the page.

waitForElementNotVisible.name: wait for element not visible
waitForElementNotVisible.description: Wait for a target element to not be visible on the page.

waitForElementPresent.name: wait for element present
waitForElementPresent.description: Wait for a target element to be present on the page.

waitForElementVisible.name: wait for element visible
waitForElementVisible.description: Wait for a target element to be visible on the page.

while.name: while
while.description: Create a loop that executes the proceeding commands repeatedly for as long as the provided conditional expression is true.
